    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-07T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-07T21:00:00-05:00" n="424"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/239: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-08T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 8, 1930—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 8—1:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>312. Shanghai’s May 3, noon.<note n="20" xml:id="d424fn20">Not printed.</note>
                    Senior Minister has telegraphed to the Senior Consul at Shanghai informing him
                    of the Diplomatic Body’s approval of the resolution passed by the ratepayers to
                    increase the <pb facs="0448" n="350" xml:id="pg_350"/> Chinese members of the
                    Municipal Council from 3 to 5.<note n="21" xml:id="d424fn21">Chinese
                        representation was increased from 3 to 5 councilors in 1930.</note> In this
                    connection Minister Johnson at Nanking has telegraphed the Legation as follows:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I approve of resolution. Please inform the Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
